courses.learning_outcomes:
To Understand:
1. the latest epidemiology of dementia, its risk factors, and that majority of dementia (e.g. Alzheimer’s disease, cerebrovascular disease) may be prevented;
2. the importance of control in cardiovascular risk factors and other life-style measures (e.g. exercise, leisure activities, diet) in the prevention of dementia;
3. certain medical legal issues, e.g. enduring power of attorney, advanced directives, that are relevant to dementia
4. the latest advances with respect to the medical treatment of Alzheimer’s disease;
5. the role of occupational and physiotherapists in the management of cognitive disorders;
6. the types of food that are considered to be healthy or harmful to the brain.
